Then Jannes and Jambres were cast down and their magic was brought to nothing before the power of YHWH. They confessed that the finger of God was at work and that they could not stand against the servant of the Most High. And they perished in the Red Sea with the host of Pharaoh, for the judgment of YHWH overtook them.
The Lord YHWH hardened the heart of Pharaoh through the words of Jannes and Jambres, yet in the end their sorcery failed and the power of the Most High prevailed. Moses stretched out his hand and the sea returned upon the Egyptians, and Jannes and Jambres were swallowed up with them.
And it came to pass that when the plagues increased, Jannes and Jambres said to Pharaoh: “This is the finger of God.” But Pharaoh would not listen, for his heart was hardened. Then the Lord brought the final judgment upon Egypt and upon the two magicians who had opposed His servant Moses.
Thus the wickedness of Jannes and Jambres was exposed before all Israel. Their enchantments could not stand before the signs and wonders wrought by the hand of YHWH through Moses and Aaron. And their names became a proverb for those who resist the living God.

